 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">where \left({{m}_{1}},{{m}_{2}},\ldots,{{m}_{n-2}}\right) is an increasing sequence constructed with the elements of \left\{1,2,\ldots,n\right\}\backslash \left\{\,j,k\right\}. The E_{{{\mu}_{{{m}_{_{1}}}}}{{\mu}_{{{m}_{_{2}}}}}\ldots {{\mu}_{{{m}_{_{n-2}}}}}}^{(k,n,j)} tensors, 11: #cqgaa60f1fn11 are built from the rank (0,n-2) contractions of the building blocks</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\begin{equation*} \begin{align*} \begin{eqnarray}&amp;&amp;{{g}_{{{\mu}_{1}}{{\mu}_{2}}}},\quad \quad {{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}},\quad \quad \left(\underset{i=1}{\overset{r-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{r}}}},\quad \quad r=2,3,\ldots,n-1.\end{eqnarray} \end{align*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\tag{ A.30 }</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\end{equation*} To show this, first note that the contraction pattern for j = 1, that is</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\begin{equation*} \begin{align*} \begin{eqnarray}&amp;&amp;{{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{1}}}}{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}\left(\underset{i=2}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}},\end{eqnarray} \end{align*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\tag{ A.31 }</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
