 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\end{equation*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">can be reduced to the j = 2 term added with some terms involving the (n-2) order term {{\nabla}^{n-3}}\xi after changing the order of the first two covariant derivatives as</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\begin{equation*} \begin{align*} \begin{eqnarray}\begin{array}{*{35}{l}} {{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{1}}}}{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{2}}}}\left(\underset{i=3}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}}= &amp; {{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{1}}}}\left[{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}},{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{2}}}}\right]\left(\underset{i=3}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}}+{{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{1}}}}{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{2}}}}{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}\left(\underset{i=3}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}} \\ = &amp; {{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{1}}}}\underset{s=3}{\overset{n-1}{\sum}}\,R_{{{\mu}_{1}}{{\mu}_{2}}{{\mu}_{s}}}^{{}}{}_{{}}^{{{\mu}_{n+1}}}{{\,}^{{}}}\left(\underset{{{i}_{1}}=3}{\overset{s-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{{{i}_{_{1}}}}}}}\right){{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{n+1}}}}\left(\underset{{{i}_{2}}=s+1}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{{{i}_{_{2}}}}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}} \\ {} &amp; +\,{{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{1}}}}R_{{{\mu}_{1}}{{\mu}_{2}}{{\mu}_{n}}}^{{}}{}_{{}}^{{{\mu}_{n+1}}}{{\,}^{{}}}\left(\underset{i=3}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n+1}}}} \\ {} &amp; +\,{{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{1}}}}{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{2}}}}{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}\left(\underset{i=3}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}}, \end{array}\end{eqnarray} \end{align*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\tag{ A.32 }</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\end{equation*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">where using {{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{1}}}}{{R}_{{{\mu}_{1}}{{\mu}_{2}}{{\mu}_{3}}{{\mu}_{4}}}}=\frac{R}{D(D-1)}\left({{\lambda}_{{{\mu}_{3}}}}{{g}_{{{\mu}_{2}}{{\mu}_{4}}}}-{{\lambda}_{{{\mu}_{4}}}}{{g}_{{{\mu}_{2}}{{\mu}_{3}}}}\right), one arrives at</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\begin{equation*} \begin{align*} \begin{eqnarray}\begin{array}{*{35}{l}} {} &amp; {{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{1}}}}{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{2}}}}\left(\underset{i=3}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}} \\ = &amp; \frac{R}{D(D-1)}\left[{{\lambda}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}}\left(\underset{i=3}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{2}}}}+\underset{s=3}{\overset{n-1}{\sum}}\,{{\lambda}_{{{\mu}_{s}}}}\left(\underset{{{i}_{1}}=3}{\overset{s-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{{{i}_{_{1}}}}}}}\right){{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{2}}}}\left(\underset{{{i}_{2}}=s+1}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{{{i}_{_{2}}}}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}}\right] \\ {} &amp; -\frac{R}{D(D-1)}{{g}_{{{\mu}_{2}}{{\mu}_{n}}}}{{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{n+1}}}}\left(\underset{i=3}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n+1}}}} \\ {} &amp; -\frac{R}{D(D-1)}\underset{s=3}{\overset{n-1}{\sum}}\,{{g}_{{{\mu}_{2}}{{\mu}_{s}}}}{{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{n+1}}}}\left(\underset{{{i}_{1}}=3}{\overset{s-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{{{i}_{_{1}}}}}}}\right){{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{n+1}}}}\left(\underset{{{i}_{2}}=s+1}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{{{i}_{_{2}}}}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}} \\ {} &amp; +{{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{1}}}}{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{2}}}}{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}\left(\underset{i=3}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}}. \end{array}\end{eqnarray} \end{align*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\tag{ A.33 }</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\end{equation*} The first line is λ-reducible and involves the n - 2 order term {{\nabla}^{n-3}}\xi, the second and the third lines involve all one-λ contraction patterns of {{\nabla}^{n-3}}\xi, that is</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\begin{equation*} \begin{align*} \begin{eqnarray}&amp;&amp;{{\lambda}^{{{\nu}_{j}}}}\left(\underset{i=1}{\overset{n-3}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\nu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\nu}_{n-2}}}},\end{eqnarray} \end{align*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\tag{ A.34 }</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\end{equation*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">with all possible j&apos;s from 1 to n - 2, and the last line is the j = 2 contraction pattern of {{\nabla}^{n-1}}\xi. Assuming {{\lambda}^{{{\nu}_{j}}}}\left({\prod}_{i=1}^{n-3}{{\nabla}_{{{\nu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\nu}_{n-2}}}} is also λ-reducible, then the j = 1 contraction pattern of {{\nabla}^{n-1}}\xi is λ-reducible if and only if the j = 2 contraction pattern of {{\nabla}^{n-1}}\xi is λ-reducible. Let us move on to the analysis of the 1&lt;j\leqslant n contraction patterns of {{\nabla}^{n-1}}\xi and let us write</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\begin{equation*} \begin{align*} \begin{eqnarray}\begin{array}{*{35}{l}} {{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{j}}}}{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}\left(\underset{i=2}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}}= &amp; {{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}\left[{{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{j}}}}\left(\underset{i=2}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}}\right]-\left({{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}{{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{j}}}}\right)\left(\underset{i=2}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}} \\ = &amp; {{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}\left[{{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{j}}}}\left(\underset{i=2}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}}\right] \\ {} &amp; -\,\frac{1}{2}{{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}{{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{j}}}}\left(\underset{i=2}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}}-\frac{1}{2}{{\lambda}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}{{\xi}^{{{\mu}_{j}}}}\left(\underset{i=2}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}}, \end{array}\end{eqnarray} \end{align*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\tag{ A.35 }</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\end{equation*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">where the last term is already λ-reducible while the first and the second terms involve the order n - 1 term {{\nabla}^{n-2}}\xi which, from the assumption (, A.27: #cqgaa60f1eqn102), has the form, 12: #cqgaa60f1fn12</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\begin{equation*} \begin{align*} \begin{eqnarray}&amp;&amp;{{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{j}}}}\left(\underset{i=2}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}}=\underset{\begin{array}{c} k=2 \\ (k\ne j) \end{array}}{\overset{n}{\sum}}\,{{\lambda}_{{{\mu}_{k}}}}E_{{{\mu}_{{{m}_{_{1}}}}}{{\mu}_{{{m}_{_{2}}}}}\ldots {{\mu}_{{{m}_{_{n-3}}}}}}^{(k-1,n-1,j-1)},\end{eqnarray} \end{align*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\tag{ A.36 }</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\end{equation*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">where \left({{m}_{1}},{{m}_{2}},\ldots,{{m}_{n-3}}\right) is an increasing sequence constructed from \left\{2,3,\ldots,n\right\}\backslash \left\{\,j,k\right\}. Using this form, one finds</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\begin{equation*} \begin{align*} \begin{eqnarray}\begin{array}{*{35}{l}} {{\lambda}^{{{\mu}_{j}}}}{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}\left(\underset{i=2}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}}= &amp; \frac{1}{2}{{\lambda}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}\left[\underset{\begin{array}{c} k=2 \\ (k\ne j) \end{array}}{\overset{n}{\sum}}\,{{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{k}}}}E_{{{\mu}_{{{m}_{_{1}}}}}{{\mu}_{{{m}_{_{2}}}}}\ldots {{\mu}_{{{m}_{_{n-3}}}}}}^{(k-1,n-1,j-1)}-{{\xi}^{{{\mu}_{j}}}}\left(\underset{i=2}{\overset{n-1}{\prod}}\,{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{i}}}}\right){{\xi}_{{{\mu}_{n}}}}\right] \\ {} &amp; +\underset{\begin{array}{c} k=2 \\ (k\ne j) \end{array}}{\overset{n}{\sum}}\,{{\lambda}_{{{\mu}_{k}}}}{{\nabla}_{{{\mu}_{1}}}}E_{{{\mu}_{{{m}_{_{1}}}}}{{\mu}_{{{m}_{_{2}}}}}\ldots {{\mu}_{{{m}_{_{n-3}}}}}}^{(k-1,n-1,j-1)}, \end{array}\end{eqnarray} \end{align*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\tag{ A.37 }</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
