 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="o">6</subfield>
  <subfield code="m">Here, the relation between the effective cosmological constant \Lambda and the AdS radius \ell is given as \begin{equation*} \begin{align*} \begin{eqnarray}&amp;&amp;\begin{array}{*{35}{l}} -\frac{1}{{{\ell}^{2}}}\equiv \frac{2 \Lambda }{(D-1)(D-2)}. \end{array}\end{eqnarray} \end{align*} \end{equation*}</subfield>
